## Figure 3 — Radar plot: sensor "signature" per FAC group

A radar plot gives a compact visual signature of each FAC group across the 5 sensors. For each group we show:

- **Branches (5)**: one per sensor (LF, RF, LW, RW, SA)
- **Central point on each branch**: median cadence of that sensor within the group
- **Connecting polygon**: links the 5 medians, forming the group signature
- **Continuous shaded ring**: median ± 1 standard deviation, shown as a filled polygon around the median line

This is an intuitive way to compare the three FAC groups at a glance. A compact polygon with narrow shading = sensors agree tightly; a distorted polygon with wide shading = sensors disagree.

```{r viz-radar-data}
# Compute median + SD per (FAC_group, sensor)
# The 5 branches are fixed in the order LF, RF, LW, RW, SA to keep the shape consistent.
sensor_order <- c("LF", "RF", "LW", "RW", "SA")

radar_stats <- df_viz %>%
  mutate(sensor = factor(sensor, levels = sensor_order)) %>%
  group_by(FAC_group, sensor) %>%
  summarise(
    median_val = median(cadence, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_val     = sd(cadence, na.rm = TRUE),
    n          = n(),
    .groups    = "drop"
  ) %>%
  # Groups with n=1 have SD=NA; replace with 0 for plotting (no shading)
  mutate(sd_val = ifelse(is.na(sd_val), 0, sd_val),
         lower  = pmax(median_val - sd_val, 0),   # clamp at 0 (cadence >= 0)
         upper  = median_val + sd_val)

cat("-- Radar statistics: median \u00B1 SD per sensor per FAC group --\n")
print(radar_stats %>% mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~ round(.x, 3))))

write_csv(radar_stats, file.path(OUTPUT_DIR, "radar_median_sd.csv"))
```

```{r viz-radar-plot, fig.width=11, fig.height=5}
# Build the radar data: we need to close the polygon by repeating the first row.
# We use coord_polar() on a categorical x-axis (sensor), with the trick
# to have a closed shape by duplicating the first point at the end.

close_polygon <- function(df) {
  first_row <- df %>% filter(sensor == sensor_order[1]) %>% mutate(sensor_num = length(sensor_order) + 1)
  df <- df %>% mutate(sensor_num = as.integer(sensor))
  bind_rows(df, first_row)
}

radar_closed <- radar_stats %>%
  group_by(FAC_group) %>%
  group_modify(~ close_polygon(.x)) %>%
  ungroup()

# We facet by FAC_group (3 panels side by side), each with its own radar.
p_radar <- ggplot(radar_closed, aes(x = sensor_num, y = median_val,
                                     group = FAC_group, color = FAC_group, fill = FAC_group)) +
  # SD band (continuous)
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), alpha = 0.20, color = NA) +
  # Median polygon
  geom_polygon(alpha = 0, linewidth = 0.9) +
  # Median points
  geom_point(aes(x = sensor_num, y = median_val), size = 3) +
  # Convert to polar coordinates
  coord_polar(start = -pi/5, clip = "off") +
  # x-axis: ticks at each sensor, labels LF/RF/LW/RW/SA
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:length(sensor_order),
                     labels = sensor_order,
